cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the robustness of online social networks and their performance under attacks, which falls under the scope of cs.SI.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper also explores the performance of elasticity on Internet topologies, which falls under the scope of cs.NI.
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses the onset of cryptic malicious attacks and their impact on network robustness, which falls under the scope of cs.CR.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the capacity of a network to maintain functionality in the advent of classical component failures, which falls under the scope of cs.SY.
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents a novel metric, elasticity, which is a link in the chain of network robustness and involves complex analysis, which falls under the scope of cs.DS.
